        "title": "Header Manager usage in Sampler",
        "body": "<p>I have a jmx script in which I have a header manager for each soap request.\nI want to extract the SOAPAction fields which has a value :<strong>\"http://****.svc\"<\/strong>\nand give it as name to the http sampler.<\/p>\n\n<p>Will i need to code to access it, if yes then how ?<\/p>\n\n<p>Are header manager fields variables/properties which can be used ?<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 49883596,
        "tags": ["java"],
        "score": 0,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 156,
        "last_edit_date": 1524025145
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [{
        "owner": {
            "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/936c09c1cf2b6492c0d59833be11a8bc?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
            "account_id": 3460456,
            "user_type": "registered",
            "user_id": 2897748,
            "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2897748/dmitri-t",
            "reputation": 168898,
            "display_name": "Dmitri T"
        },
        "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
        "score": 1,
        "is_accepted": false,
        "last_activity_date": 1523987251,
        "creation_date": 1523987251,
        "body": "<ol>\n<li>Add <a href=\"http://jmeter.apache.org/usermanual/component_reference.html#JSR223_PostProcessor\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">JSR223 PostProcessor<\/a> to be <a href=\"https://www.blazemeter.com/blog/jmeter-scoping-rules-the-ultimate-guide\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">in scope of the requests<\/a> you would like to modify<\/li>\n<li><p>Put the following code into \"Script\" area:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>for (int i = 0; i &lt; sampler.getHeaderManager().size(); i++) {\n    def header = sampler.getHeaderManager().getHeader(i)\n    if (header.getName().equals('SOAPAction')) {\n        prev.setSampleLabel(header.getValue())\n        break\n    }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre><\/li>\n<li>Enjoy<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n",
        "answer_id": 49884454,
        "question_id": 49883596
    }],
